17/01/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A government delegation led by Prime Minister Ivo Sanader is in Brussels on Monday (17 January) for meetings with top EU officials. According to a cabinet statement over the weekend, the discussions will focus on the pace of preparations for launching EU accession negotiations with Croatia. EU leaders have set 17 March as the date for starting the talks, provided Zagreb demonstrates full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal. (Vecernji list - 16/01/05; Hina - 15/01/05)
